text: Noh Do-hee (Hangul: 노도희; born 13 December 1995) is a South Korean short track speed skater. Two-time overall world junior champion Noh was called up to the South Korean senior national team squad for the 2014–15 season, and had two podium finishes in the 1500 metres at the 2014–15 World Cup events. At the 2015 World Short Track Speed Skating Championships, she won a gold medal as part of the South Korean 3000 metre relay team. ==External links== * Noh Do- hee at ShorttrackOnLine.info Category:1995 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean female short track speed skaters Category:Asian Games gold medalists for South Korea Category:Asian Games medalists in short track speed skating Category:Short track speed skaters at the 2017 Asian Winter Games Category:Medalists at the 2017 Asian Winter Games Category:World Short Track Speed Skating Championships medalists Category:Universiade medalists in short track speed skating Category:Universiade gold medalists for South Korea Category:Competitors at the 2017 Winter Universiade
